parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, and can leave the driver stranded. This issue can also cause anxiety and safety concerns, especially when transporting infants or other vulnerable passengers.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the vehicle shakes or makes loud noises
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle may not start
the engine may rattle or stall
the vehicle may shut off completely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. This issue can also cause safety concerns, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle may not start
the engine may rattle or stall
the vehicle may shut off completely
DTC code P0087000 indicates inadequate fuel pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective engine can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver. This issue can also cause safety concerns, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine stalls or loses power
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle may not start
the engine may rattle or stall
the vehicle may shut off completely
cylinder chamber not creating enough pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate repair and customer service can cause frustration and anxiety for the driver, especially when the vehicle is left unrepaired for an extended period.
symptoms: The dealer is unable to diagnose or repair the issue
the driver is left without a vehicle for an extended period
no loaner or rental car is provided
the manufacturer is unresponsive to concerns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded in a hazardous location.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
often at low speeds or when entering roadways
and may not accelerate properly; dashboard lights may come on when the vehicle shuts off; the vehicle may not allow acceleration after shutting off.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Pretensioner Failure and Recall Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt pretensioner can lead to inadequate restraint in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality. Delays in recall repairs can leave drivers vulnerable to safety risks.
symptoms: The seat belt does not retract properly
has excessive slack
requires multiple tugs or hard pulls to fully retract
and may not provide adequate protection in the event of a crash or accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Recall Repair and Parts Distribution
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to obtain timely recall repairs can leave drivers at risk due to unresolved safety issues. Inadequate parts distribution and repair processes can exacerbate the problem.
symptoms: Delayed or unavailable recall repairs
lack of communication from manufacturers or dealerships
and inadequate solutions provided by dealerships.
